From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000023 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 23:50:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: OMAP4: omap_twl: don't latch a failed SMPS_OFFSET efuse
 read; seed steelhead

The TWL6030 SMPS_OFFSET efuse is read lazily on the first vsel/uv
conversion. That first conversion happens in omap_vc_init_channel()
(a late_initcall, ~0.77 s) -- long before the DT-probed twl-core i2c
device is up (~3.9 s) -- so the read fails ("twl: not initialized"),
yet the code latched is_offset_valid anyway. The efuse was then treated
as all-zero forever: ES1.0 voltage scale, ceiling 1 316 660 uV. The VC
channel init for VDD_IVA/VDD_CORE converts the OMAP4 blanket ON/ONLP
voltage of 1 375 000 uV, which then logs

  twl6030_uv_to_vsel:OUT OF RANGE! non mapped vsel for 1375000 Vs max 1316660

four times per boot (2 domains x on/onlp) and falls back to vsel 0x3A
(1.35 V) -- a latent under-volt on any future VC-driven wake.

Fix the latch: only mark the cached value valid when the i2c read
succeeded, so the real efuse is picked up once twl-core has probed.
For the interim window on steelhead (Nexus Q), seed the value read
live from this unit's efuse (0x7f -- bit3 set, i.e. the ES1.1+
0.7-1.4 V scale with ceiling 1 417 960 uV), which maps 1 375 000 uV to
a valid vsel and makes the init-time PRM_VC_VAL_CMD programming
correct.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_twl.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_twl.c
@@ -14,6 +14,7 @@
 #include <linux/io.h>
 #include <linux/kernel.h>
 #include <linux/mfd/twl.h>
+#include <linux/of.h>
 #include <linux/workqueue.h>
 
 #include "soc.h"
@@ -55,6 +56,35 @@
 
 #define REG_SMPS_OFFSET         0xE0
 
+static void twl6030_read_smps_offset(void)
+{
+	if (is_offset_valid)
+		return;
+
+	if (!twl_i2c_read_u8(TWL6030_MODULE_ID0, &smps_offset,
+			     REG_SMPS_OFFSET)) {
+		is_offset_valid = true;
+		return;
+	}
+
+	/*
+	 * The efuse is read lazily, and the first conversions run from
+	 * omap_vc_init_channel() (late_initcall) long before the DT-probed
+	 * twl-core i2c device is up, so the read above fails there ("twl:
+	 * not initialized"). Mainline latched is_offset_valid even then,
+	 * permanently treating the efuse as all-zero (ES1.0 scale, max
+	 * 1 316 660 uV) - the 1 375 000 uV ON/ONLP voltages of the IVA/CORE
+	 * VC channels then logged "OUT OF RANGE!" and mis-mapped to vsel
+	 * 0x3A (1.35 V). Do NOT latch on failure, so the real efuse is read
+	 * once twl-core has probed; until then, on steelhead, seed the
+	 * conversions with this unit's real efuse value (0x7f, read live
+	 * over i2c 2026-07-02: bit3 set => 0.7-1.4 V scale, max
+	 * 1 417 960 uV, so 1 375 000 uV maps to a valid vsel).
+	 */
+	if (of_machine_is_compatible("google,steelhead"))
+		smps_offset = 0x7f;
+}
+
 static unsigned long twl4030_vsel_to_uv(const u8 vsel)
 {
 	return (((vsel * 125) + 6000)) * 100;
@@ -75,11 +105,7 @@
 	 * is programmed to all 0's where as starting from
 	 * TWL6030 ES1.1 the efuse is programmed to 1
 	 */
-	if (!is_offset_valid) {
-		twl_i2c_read_u8(TWL6030_MODULE_ID0, &smps_offset,
-				REG_SMPS_OFFSET);
-		is_offset_valid = true;
-	}
+	twl6030_read_smps_offset();
 
 	if (!vsel)
 		return 0;
@@ -109,11 +135,7 @@
 	 * is programmed to all 0's where as starting from
 	 * TWL6030 ES1.1 the efuse is programmed to 1
 	 */
-	if (!is_offset_valid) {
-		twl_i2c_read_u8(TWL6030_MODULE_ID0, &smps_offset,
-				REG_SMPS_OFFSET);
-		is_offset_valid = true;
-	}
+	twl6030_read_smps_offset();
 
 	if (!uv)
 		return 0x00;
